<subSubSection id="07E113A1FFC1485CFF4ED483FEE22997" box="[151,332,187,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF4ED483FEE22997" blockId="10.[151,524,151,213]" box="[151,332,187,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFF4ED483FEB92997" box="[151,279,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 49–61</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFEFBD483FEE22997" box="[290,332,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 107" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,992,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-352@19.[178,1409,992,1958]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 107. Geographical records of Cephalops species in Colombia. Cephalops acutus sp. nov., C. amapaensis, C. gracilis sp. nov., C. klinsmanni sp. nov. and C. lobatus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592686/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">107</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07E113A1FFC1485CFF4ED53BFC2F2B5B" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF4ED53BFC2F2B5B" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF4ED53BFEBC285F" bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Antenna with scape and pedicel brown, postpedicel dark brown, slightly acute. Frontal triangle with conspicuous dark brown callus. Coxae dark brown, trochanters light brown, tibiae dark brown, with bases and apices light brown. Abdomen ground color dark brown, tergite 1 sparsely velvety light brown pruinose, with four brown and long setae laterally; tergites 2–5 velvety dark brown anteriorly, brown pruinose posteriorly and laterally, with conspicuous setae. Surstyli subsymmetrical, slightly subequal to epandrium length, completely setose; thickened at base, thin apically, with tips slightly inward directed. Apex of phallic guide stout, long, thickened at base, acute apically. Phallus trifid, with ducts distinctly separated only in distal 1/3, only tips of ejaculatory ducts slightly coiled. Ejaculatory apodeme funnel-shaped, with sinuous margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07E113A1FFC1485CFF1ED61BFA9E2C73" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="description">
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF1ED61BFA9E2C73" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF1ED61BFEF72B7F" bold="true" box="[199,345,547,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Description.</emphasis>
MALE (
<typeStatus id="9040FE88FFC1485CFE1BD61BFD852B7C" box="[450,555,547,574]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">holotype</typeStatus>
). Body length 
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFC1485CFD0AD61BFC812B7C" box="[723,815,547,574]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFCE2D61BFCD72B7C" bold="true" box="[827,889,547,574]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFC53D61BFBBE2B7C" box="[906,1040,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 49–50</figureCitation>
). Eyes contiguous for 19 facets. F, EM, V (mm) = 0.5, 0.5, 0.2. Frontal triangle black-brown pruinose, with conspicuous dark brown callus. Postcranium brown, ventrally gray pruinose, dorsally brown pruinose. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFC07D653FB9F2BC4" box="[990,1073,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
) with pedicel dark brown, with three setae dorsally and three longer setae ventrally; postpedicel dark brown, with acuminate apex. LPP/WPP = 2.7. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF4ED68BFF432B8C" bold="true" box="[151,237,691,718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFF24D68BFE032B8C" box="[253,429,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 49–50, 52</figureCitation>
). Postpronotal lobe dark brown. Scutum dark brown, gray-brown pruinose. Notopleuron concolorous with scutum, gray-brown pruinose. Scutellum brown, gray-brown pruinose, with few tiny setae scattered and 12 inconspicuous setae along posterior margin, two stouter. Mesopleuron and mediotergite brown, graybrown pruinose. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFE8CD727FE3C2A7B" bold="true" box="[341,402,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFE7BD727FE582A78" box="[418,502,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). Length 
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFC1485CFDB8D727FD142A78" box="[609,698,799,826]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="mm" value="6.4">6.4 mm</quantity>
. LW/MWW = 3.1; LTC/LFC = 1.6. Membrane brown infuscated; vein r-m located slightly after basal third of upper section of cell dm; anal lobe normal. Halter stem light brown, except base and apex dark brown, knob dark brown. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFD2FD75FFC822AC3" bold="true" box="[758,812,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFCE7D75FFC3A2AC3" box="[830,916,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Coxae dark brown; trochanters light brown; femora brown, with apices light brown, with long setae ventrally and a row of long and fine yellow setae posterolaterally; tibiae dark brown, with bases and apices light brown; tarsomeres 1–4 light brown, 5 dark brown; pulvilli light brown. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF34D7EBFEF52AAC" bold="true" box="[237,347,979,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFEB3D7EBFDB82AAC" box="[362,534,979,1006]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 49–50, 54</figureCitation>
). Ground color velvety dark brown, tergite 1 sparsely light brown pruinose, with four brown and long setae laterally; tergites 2–5 dark brown anteriorly, brown pruinose posterior and laterally, with conspicuous setae; tergites and sternites 6 and 7 as in 
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFCD9D023FCFA2D74" box="[768,852,1051,1078]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
. Syntergosternite 8 brown, brown pruinose, shorter than length of tergite 5, with membranous area apically (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFCFFD007FC002D18" box="[806,942,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 54, 56</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="88FB3BA9FFC1485CFC1DD007FBED2D18" box="[964,1091,1087,1114]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Terminalia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFC1DD007FBED2D18" bold="true" box="[964,1091,1087,1114]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Terminalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFB8AD007FB762D18" box="[1107,1240,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 55–61</figureCitation>
). Epandrium and surstyli dark brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFEA7D05BFE7C2D3C" box="[382,466,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
). Surstyli (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFD90D05BFD672D3C" box="[585,713,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 56–58</figureCitation>
) subsymmetrical, slightly equal to epandrium length, completely setose; thickened at base, thin apically, with tips slightly inward-directed, left surstylus slightly shorter than right (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFF79D093FF5B2D84" box="[160,245,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
); both surstyli with margins straight, tips forward directed when seen in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFB64D093FAEF2D84" box="[1213,1345,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Figs 57–58</figureCitation>
). Gonopods subsymmetrical, right gonopod slightly thicker than left (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFC96D0F7FC0D2DA8" box="[847,931,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Apex of phallic guide stout, long, thickened at base, acute apically (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFE43D0CBFE402C4C" box="[410,494,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme funnel-shaped, with sinuous margins (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFB47D0CBFB5E2C4C" box="[1182,1264,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Phallus trifid, with ducts distinctly separated only in distal 1/3, only tips slightly coiled (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFC0DD12FFB862C70" box="[980,1064,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). FEMALE. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
