<subSubSection id="07E113A1FFC1485CFF1ED1F3FECB2E9F" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF1ED1F3FE772F48" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF1ED1F3FEE02CA7" bold="true" box="[199,334,1483,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after Klinsmann Steeven Ramos Vargas, the son of the first author. Specific epithet in genitive case.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF1ED22BFCC02F6F" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" box="[199,878,1555,1581]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF1ED22BFDAB2F6F" bold="true" box="[199,517,1555,1581]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="37EC00BAFFC1485CFDD5D22BFDD42F6F" box="[524,634,1555,1581]" name="Colombia" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="8D3F8EC8FFC1485CFD50D22BFD462F6F" box="[649,744,1555,1581]" country="Colombia" name="Caqueta" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Caquetá</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFD26D22BFCCF2F6F" box="[767,865,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 107" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,992,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-352@19.[178,1409,992,1958]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 107. Geographical records of Cephalops species in Colombia. Cephalops acutus sp. nov., C. amapaensis, C. gracilis sp. nov., C. klinsmanni sp. nov. and C. lobatus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592686/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF1ED20FFEE22F37" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF1ED20FFE842F13" bold="true" box="[199,298,1591,1617]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Habitat.</emphasis>
The specimens were collected in the cloudy forest of the eastern cordillera in the Colombian Andean Amazon region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F44402AFFC1485CFF1ED247FECB2E9F" blockId="10.[151,1437,259,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFF1ED247FE372FDB" bold="true" box="[199,409,1663,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="88FB3BA9FFC1485CFE7BD247FD302FDB" authority="Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Marques &amp; Rafael, 2022" authorityName="Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Marques &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2022" box="[418,670,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Cephalops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klinsmanni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFE7BD247FD302FDB" box="[418,670,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Cephalops klinsmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFD7ED247FCAC2FDB" bold="true" box="[679,770,1663,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="66BC2143FFC1485CFD7ED247FCAC2FDB" box="[679,770,1663,1689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
runs to 
<taxonomicName id="88FB3BA9FFC1485CFCBDD2B8FB1F2FD8" authority="Hardy, 1954" authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="1954" box="[868,1201,1663,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Pipunculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villifemoralis">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFCBDD2B8FCD92FD8" box="[868,887,1664,1690]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFC5FD247FBB52FDB" box="[902,1051,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">villifemoralis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B6A3DDBFFC1485CFBFCD247FB1F2FD8" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1061,1201,1663,1690]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref18896" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1954) Neotropical Dorilaidae studies, Part III. Brazilian species and key to the known species of Dorilas sens. lat. Boletim do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 123, 1 - 60." type="journal article" year="1954">
Hardy, 
<quantity id="8803EDCFFFC1485CFBA0D247FB1F2FD8" box="[1145,1201,1663,1690]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.96316" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" unit="in" value="1954.0">1954</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the couplet 14 of the key presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="2B6A3DDBFFC1485CFE5CD29BFD8C2FFF" author="Rafael, J. A." box="[389,546,1699,1725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" pagination="353 - 390" refId="ref19665" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1990) Revisao das especies neotropicais do genero Cephalops Fallen (Diptera: Pipunculidae). Acta Amazonica, 20, 353 - 390." type="journal article" year="1990">Rafael (1990)</bibRefCitation>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="88FB3BA9FFC1485CFD0BD29CFC262FFF" authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="1954" box="[722,904,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Pipunculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villifemoralis">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFD0BD29CFD4B2FFC" box="[722,741,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFD2AD29BFC262FFF" box="[755,904,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">villifemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having postpedicel dark brown (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFACFD29CFAF02FFF" box="[1302,1374,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">versus</emphasis>
postpedicel yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="88FB3BA9FFC1485CFEBCD2F0FDB32FA3" authorityName="Hardy" authorityYear="1954" box="[357,541,1735,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Pipunculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villifemoralis">
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFEBCD2F0FED62FA0" box="[357,376,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFE51D2FFFDB32FA3" box="[392,541,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">villifemoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); all coxae dark brown (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFCE3D2FFFC232FA3" box="[826,909,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
) (
<emphasis id="7D8F9C38FFC1485CFC71D2F0FC5E2FA3" box="[936,1008,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">versus</emphasis>
hind coxa light brown); both surstyli thickened at the base, thin apically, with tips slightly inward directed, left surstylus slightly shorter than right (
<figureCitation id="D7C05CAFFFC1485CFAB6D2D3FF1A2E68" captionStart="FIGURES 49–61" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[151,1436,181,1731]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 49–61. Cephalops klinsmanni sp. nov. (LEUA–M8677). Male. 49, Habitus, left lateral view; 50, Habitus, dorsal view; 51, Antenna; 52, Thorax, dorsal view; 53, Wing; 54, Abdomen, dorsal view; 55, Tergites and sternites 6 and 7, ventral view; 56, Terminalia, dorsal view; 57, Left surstylus, lateral view; 58, Right surstylus, lateral view; 59, Hypandrium and gonopods, ventral view, 60, Phallic guide and phallus, left lateral view; 61, Ejaculatory apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592664/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="211">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) [
